<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" media="screen" href="/~d/styles/rss2full.xsl"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/css" media="screen" href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~d/styles/itemcontent.css"?><rss xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:wfw="http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:sy="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/" xmlns:slash="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/" version="2.0"><channel><title>UNWIRE.HK</title><link>https://unwire.hk</link><description /><lastBuildDate>Mon, 10 Jan 2022 11:26:34 +0000</lastBuildDate><language>zh-TW</language><sy:updatePeriod>hourly	</sy:updatePeriod><sy:updateFrequency>1	</sy:updateFrequency><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/unwirelife" /><feedburner:info xmlns:feedburner="http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0" uri="unwirelife" /><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="hub" href="http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/" /><item><title>美國大學研 3D 打印新技術，可打印 OLED 顯示面板</title><link>https://unwire.hk/2022/01/10/we-can-now-3d-print-oled-screens/3d-%e6%89%93%e5%8d%b0/?utm_source=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=we-can-now-3d-print-oled-screens</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[高威]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 10 Jan 2022 11:25:23 +0000</pubDate><category><![CDATA[3D 打印]]></category><guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1080444</guid><description><![CDATA[<p>相信大家對 3D Printing 技術毫不陌生，但最近的明尼蘇達雙城大學 (University of Mi [&#8230;]</p></p>]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>相信大家對 3D Printing 技術毫不陌生，但最近的明尼蘇達雙城大學 (University of Minnesota Twin Cities) 研究人員研究了一款以 3D 打印技術所製成的彈性 OLED 顯示面板，而且其大小還可以自行訂定，將來用家或許可以自行打印並修理所需替換的組件。<a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Fully_3D_Printed_OLED_Display.png"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1080446" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Fully_3D_Printed_OLED_Display-694x382.png" alt="" width="694" height="382" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Fully_3D_Printed_OLED_Display-694x382.png 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Fully_3D_Printed_OLED_Display-768x422.png 768w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Fully_3D_Printed_OLED_Display.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p>研究人員表示，新的方法結合了兩種 3D 打印方式，製作出六層功能顯示器（Functional Display）。團隊首先以推料式（Extrusion Printing）印製電極、封裝、絕緣體和連接器，而其主動層（Active Layers）則以室溫噴灑出來。過往研究團隊曾經遇到光均勻度（Light Uniformity）的問題，或是太過倚重 3D 打印的方式去擺放組件，如旋轉塗佈（Spin-Coating）或熱蒸鍍（Thermal Evaporation）等。</p><p>不過現時的製成品僅有 1.5 吋闊，而且只有 64 像素，幾乎沒有任何顯示器需要只得 64 像素的面板。以一幅 1080p 的顯示器為例，已經需要超過 200 萬像素。研究人員還希望改善其發光度，而且研究人員所使用的 3D 打印機，售價比得上 Tesla 的 Model S，故此需要普及到一般使用仍然言之尚早。但此技術或可在將來令大家，不用再依賴廠商所預先裝好的組件。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/螢幕截圖-2022-01-10-下午 6.15.22.png"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1080445" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/螢幕截圖-2022-01-10-下午 6.15.22-694x461.png" alt="" width="694" height="461" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/螢幕截圖-2022-01-10-下午 6.15.22-694x461.png 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/螢幕截圖-2022-01-10-下午 6.15.22-1280x850.png 1280w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/螢幕截圖-2022-01-10-下午 6.15.22-768x510.png 768w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/螢幕截圖-2022-01-10-下午 6.15.22.png 1346w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p>來源：<a href="https://www.engadget.com/full-3d-printed-flexible-oled-display-220930099.html?src=rss&amp;fbclid=IwAR0S9MRUEZ8SgPMsxbZXOzkXFi4wbaJ7gxhAvl86a-7KV0HDvvkZ5TEzV5w">Engadget</a></p></p><div class="feedflare">
